op align=left class=m><span class=title> Favorite Variant Rules</span><hr size=1> 1) Your first hit die is always maximum. ie a level 1 warrior always has 10 hp (plus con bonus) a rogue 6 hp (plus con) etc.<br>
<br>
2) After any significant period of out-of-danger rest (between scenarios) all characters re-roll their HP.  ie a level 6 rogue with 16 con would, at the start of each session, roll 6d6+12 to determine his HP that session. (or, 5d6+18, if using rule 1 above)  Some weeks you just feel better than others.<br>
<br>
3) The GM keeps track of player HP.  <br>
<br>
